[src:bevy-ecs-rust/latest-bevy] Provides math types and functionality for the Bevy game engine.
[src:bevy-ecs-rust/latest-bevy] This crate provides ‘picking’ capabilities for the Bevy game engine, allowing pointers to interact with entities using hover, click, and drag events.
[src:bevy-ecs-rust/latest-bevy] to import common components, bundles, and plugins.
[src:bevy-ecs-rust/latest-bevy] An implementation of the Bevy Remote Protocol, to allow for remote control of a Bevy app.
[src:bevy-ecs-rust/latest-bevy] Composable scene authoring for Bevy, defined using the Bevy Scene Notation (BSN) format.
[src:bevy-ecs-rust/latest-bevy] Framework for saving and loading user settings files in Bevy applications.
[src:bevy-ecs-rust/latest-bevy] Provides 2D sprite rendering functionality.
[src:bevy-ecs-rust/latest-bevy] In Bevy, states are app-wide interdependent, finite state machines that are generally used to model the large scale structure of your program: whether a game is paused, if the player is in combat, if assets are loaded and so on.
[src:bevy-ecs-rust/latest-bevy] This crate provides the tools for positioning and rendering text in Bevy.
[src:bevy-ecs-rust/latest-bevy] This crate provides a set of standard widgets for Bevy UI, such as buttons, checkboxes, and sliders.
[src:bevy-ecs-rust/latest-bevy] These widgets have no inherent styling, it’s the responsibility of the user to add styling appropriate for their game or application.
[src:bevy-ecs-rust/latest-bevy] provides a platform-agnostic interface for windowing in Bevy.
